  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "As part of the Bazel effort, in #35453 we had to rename `build/` to `build-tools/`, as `build/` and `BUILD` conflicted on case-insensitive filesystems (like macOS).\r\n\r\nBazel 0.4.1 has now been released, which includes the fix for https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/issues/552, allowing us to use `BUILD.bazel` instead of `BUILD`.\r\n\r\nI'd like to rename `build-tools/` back to `build/`, to be consistent with how the repo has been in older releases, and I'd like to cherry-pick this into 1.5 as well, so we don't have to special case in other repos for months. It's probably too close to cherry-pick for 1.5.0, but it should be fairly safe for 1.5.1 IMO.\r\n\r\ncc @mikedanese @spxtr @thockin @saad-ali ",
